        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>There are two <ph id="ph1">`abort`</ph> flags: <ph id="ph2">`_WRITE_ABORT_MSG`</ph> and <ph id="ph3">`_CALL_REPORTFAULT`</ph>.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><ph id="ph1">`_WRITE_ABORT_MSG`</ph> determines whether a helpful text message is printed when a program is abnormally terminated.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The message states that the application has called the <ph id="ph1">`abort`</ph> function.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The default behavior is to print the message.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><ph id="ph1">`_CALL_REPORTFAULT`</ph>, if set, specifies that a Watson crash dump is generated and reported when <ph id="ph2">`abort`</ph> is called.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>By default, crash dump reporting is enabled in non-DEBUG builds.</source>
